cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper proposes a method to learn latent disease networks directly from unstructured biomedical text corpora. This involves natural language processing techniques such as text chunking and semantic similarity metrics. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper deals with the challenge of unsupervised knowledge extraction from large text corpora, which is a common problem in information retrieval. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a fully unsupervised method to learn latent disease networks, which involves machine learning techniques such as graph generation and geodesic distance calculation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method to automatically extract latent disease networks from unstructured text, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper deals with the extraction of disease networks from biomedical text corpora, which can be seen as a type of information network.
